    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@vvo I thought that a naive solution to this is to create a 'master' package that contains all the instasearch.js deps vendorized inside the same package, this way you'll have only one lodash for everything. I'm not so experienced with NPM though to know if it's possible to do.\n\nAs a quick fix, yes we could use an older lodash, but v4 is nicer and the future so I'll stick with that in my project.\n\nConcerning the size, gzip is going to make a lot of duplication go away, but webpack still has to parse those files every time when restarting the dev server/building etc.. which makes it slower. I hate slow.\n",
